cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper primarily focuses on studying the capacity of a discrete time, memoryless and complex AWGN channel in the presence of a nonlinear energy harvester at the receiver. This falls under the domain of information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless information and power transfer, which is a key aspect of communication networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The nonlinear energy harvester models considered in the paper can be seen as part of a larger system, and the study of their impact on the capacity of the channel falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless networks and the transmission of information and power over them. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The study of wireless information and power transfer can be seen as a problem in multiagent systems, where multiple agents (transmitters and receivers) interact with each other to achieve a common goal.
